Key Match Events: Jamal Musiala was once again sensational
Maximilian Mittelstadt scored a thunderbolt to level the score
Niclas Fullkrug stole the show with a late winner
Post-Match Reflections: It has been an incredible week for Germany with successive victories against two European powerhouses - France & Netherlands. Their Euro 2024 preparations are well on track
Miscellaneous Highlights: It was Fullkrug's 11th international goal in just 15 appearances. It's a quite remarkable record, considering he did not make his Germany debut until he was nearly 30 years old
Others: The Dutch defenders had a tough time keeping Jamal Musiala and Florian Wirtz in check

Matthijs de Ligt should have converted a free-kick from Daley Blind but the defender bizarrely chose to be unselfish from a scoring position and headed the ball across the goal instead of going for the target
